From 6db090b8dfddb9d090cbe4b64548bf17c67a76a0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: operations-jacrentals <operations@jacrentals.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 22:38:43 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Wire the customer Comms section that was built and never
 called (C3)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

commsCustSectionHtml() has existed, complete, with ZERO call sites — so the
one question the front desk asks most ("did we already talk to this person?")
had no answer anywhere on the Customers card. Added the single missing call.

Evidence this was an omission, not a decision:
 - the DETAIL.customers render-order comment already lists the position
   ("... -> active bar -> Comms -> Cards ..."); it is placed exactly there.
 - commsFetchMsgs' own comment names commsCustSectionHtml as one of its
   intended "displayed callers" that wants a repaint when bodies land.
 - all four CSS classes it emits (.comms-sec/.comms-line/.comms-snip/.cp-dot)
   are already present in style.css.
 - its buttons' handlers (js-comms-copen / js-comms-cend) are already live.

No new UI was authored: it reuses badge/actionPill/ghostPill and is stamped
through existing rulebook builders, so no new data-r and no WINDOW_CATALOG
entry are needed (gen-rule-usage --check and check-window-catalog both green).

Safe by construction: the function returns '' when the backend is offline or
the customer has no messages, and commsFetchMsgs is 30s-cached with in-flight
de-duplication, so opening a customer adds at most one request per 30s.

DEFERRED from this branch — tap-to-call (D1). Wrapping the phone in the
existing telHref() helper has no conflict-free home right now:
 - on the row, tapping already opens the customer record;
 - in the title band, flagEl is a shared R9 <span> builder with no href, so
   adding one changes the design system everywhere it is used;
 - in the Account section, acctField renders the value as tap-to-edit.
Each needs a designed affordance (e.g. a separate phone icon beside the
value) — a /jactec-ui call, not an implementation detail. Left for Jac.

Gates: smoke, logic-test, lease-test, lease-deploy-test, promote-test,
deck-test, cachebust-test, gen-rule-usage --check, check-window-catalog,
check-design-md, gen-code-map --check — all green. check-cachebust is red
pending the ?v= bump /deploy owns.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
